Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198906">1989-06-30 18:28:00</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626955&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626955&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

    Date: Fri, 30 Jun 89 10:35:38 EDT
    From: Roy Smith &lt;roy@alanine.phri.nyu.edu&gt;

    If I do the obvious and put a CNAME record in:

    phri.nyu.edu.	IN	CNAME	phri.phri.nyu.edu.

    I get complaints about how phri.nyu.edu has both a CNAME and other
    information, which is illegal (I'm running BIND, if that makes any
    difference).  What is the right way to do what I want to do?

I believe we do it the other way around:

gateway.think.com.	IN	CNAME	think.com.

                                                barmar

